1400824785233}, {"id": 40, "seek": 15766, "start": 169.3, "end": 171.66, "text": " tapes, solid state drives.", "tokens": [50946, 31349, 11, 5100, 1785, 11754, 13, 51064], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20306018682626578, "compression_ratio": 1.752212389380531, "no_speech_prob": 0.016161400824785233}, {"id": 41, "seek": 15766, "start": 171.66, "end": 174.38, "text": " These are all examples of secondary storage.", "tokens": [51064, 1981, 366, 439, 5110, 295, 11396, 6725, 13, 51200], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20306018682626578, "compression_ratio": 1.752212389380531, "no_speech_prob": 0.016161400824785233}, {"id": 42, "seek": 15766, "start": 174.38, "end": 178.46, "text": " They're not nearly as fast, but they can store a lot more data.", "tokens": [51200, 814, 434, 406, 6217, 382, 2370, 11, 457, 436, 393, 3531, 257, 688, 544, 1412, 13, 51404], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20306018682626578, "compression_ratio": 1.752212389380531, "no_speech_prob": 0.016161400824785233}, {"id": 43, "seek": 15766, "start": 178.46, "end": 181.57999999999998, "text": " A lot more pictures of you, cutie.", "tokens": [51404, 316, 688, 544, 5242, 295, 291, 11, 1723, 414, 13, 51560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20306018682626578, "compression_ratio": 1.752212389380531, "no_speech_prob": 0.016161400824785233}, {"id": 44, "seek": 15766, "start": 181.57999999999998, "end": 185.38, "text": " So what do we primarily use secondary storage for?", "tokens": [51560, 407, 437, 360, 321, 10029, 764, 11396, 6725, 337, 30, 51750], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20306018682626578, "compression_ratio": 1.752212389380531, "no_speech_prob": 0.016161400824785233}, {"id": 45, "seek": 18538, "start": 185.38, "end": 190.22, "text": " We use secondary storage for storing the data and the program code when it's not being", "tokens": [50364, 492, 764, 11396, 6725, 337, 26085, 264, 1412, 293, 264, 1461, 3089, 562, 309, 311, 406, 885, 50606], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 46, "seek": 18538, "start": 190.22, "end": 191.22, "text": " used.", "tokens": [50606, 1143, 13, 50656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 47, "seek": 18538, "start": 191.22, "end": 196.18, "text": " So pictures, things like that, data from programs, movies, they're stored in our secondary", "tokens": [50656, 407, 5242, 11, 721, 411, 300, 11, 1412, 490, 4268, 11, 6233, 11, 436, 434, 12187, 294, 527, 11396, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 48, "seek": 18538, "start": 196.18, "end": 197.46, "text": " storage.", "tokens": [50904, 6725, 13, 50968], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 49, "seek": 18538, "start": 197.46, "end": 202.54, "text": " Now, let's talk about one other concept and it's known as virtual memory.", "tokens": [50968, 823, 11, 718, 311, 751, 466, 472, 661, 3410, 293, 309, 311, 2570, 382, 6374, 4675, 13, 51222], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 50, "seek": 18538, "start": 202.54, "end": 206.82, "text": " And to explain virtual memory, we have to understand a little bit how a computer system", "tokens": [51222, 400, 281, 2903, 6374, 4675, 11, 321, 362, 281, 1223, 257, 707, 857, 577, 257, 3820, 1185, 51436], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 51, "seek": 18538, "start": 206.82, "end": 207.82, "text": " actually works.", "tokens": [51436, 767, 1985, 13, 51486], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 52, "seek": 18538, "start": 207.82, "end": 213.14, "text": " So you've probably noticed when you double click on an icon like Word, it actually takes", "tokens": [51486, 407, 291, 600, 1391, 5694, 562, 291, 3834, 2052, 322, 364, 6528, 411, 8725, 11, 309, 767, 2516, 51752], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18405737075130496, "compression_ratio": 1.6813186813186813, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009161328780464828}, {"id": 53, "seek": 21314, "start": 213.14, "end": 215.85999999999999, "text": " a little bit of time for that program to load.", "tokens": [50364, 257, 707, 857, 295, 565, 337, 300, 1461, 281, 3677, 13, 50500], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 54, "seek": 21314, "start": 215.85999999999999, "end": 219.94, "text": " And in fact, there's often what we call a load screen.", "tokens": [50500, 400, 294, 1186, 11, 456, 311, 2049, 437, 321, 818, 257, 3677, 2568, 13, 50704], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 55, "seek": 21314, "start": 219.94, "end": 221.85999999999999, "text": " So what is a load screen?", "tokens": [50704, 407, 437, 307, 257, 3677, 2568, 30, 50800], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 56, "seek": 21314, "start": 221.85999999999999, "end": 226.77999999999997, "text": " A load screen is where the program is telling you it's actually taking data from secondary", "tokens": [50800, 316, 3677, 2568, 307, 689, 264, 1461, 307, 3585, 291, 309, 311, 767, 1940, 1412, 490, 11396, 51046], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 57, "seek": 21314, "start": 226.77999999999997, "end": 232.33999999999997, "text": " storage, from slower hard drives, and it's moving it into RAM, into memory, much higher", "tokens": [51046, 6725, 11, 490, 14009, 1152, 11754, 11, 293, 309, 311, 2684, 309, 666, 14561, 11, 666, 4675, 11, 709, 2946, 51324], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 58, "seek": 21314, "start": 232.33999999999997, "end": 233.85999999999999, "text": " speed storage.", "tokens": [51324, 3073, 6725, 13, 51400], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 59, "seek": 21314, "start": 233.85999999999999, "end": 238.14, "text": " And the reason you want this to occur is that the processor works so incredibly quickly.", "tokens": [51400, 400, 264, 1778, 291, 528, 341, 281, 5160, 307, 300, 264, 15321, 1985, 370, 6252, 2661, 13, 51614], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 60, "seek": 21314, "start": 238.14, "end": 241.06, "text": " It's always going through calculations.", "tokens": [51614, 467, 311, 1009, 516, 807, 20448, 13, 51760], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15716842182895593, "compression_ratio": 1.6728624535315986, "no_speech_prob": 0.0025468962267041206}, {"id": 61, "seek": 24106, "start": 241.06, "end": 245.14000000000001, "text": " We've had to wait for a very long time for some data that's requested to come back from", "tokens": [50364, 492, 600, 632, 281, 1699, 337, 257, 588, 938, 565, 337, 512, 1412, 300, 311, 16436, 281, 808, 646, 490, 50568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 62, "seek": 24106, "start": 245.14000000000001, "end": 246.82, "text": " say secondary storage.", "tokens": [50568, 584, 11396, 6725, 13, 50652], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 63, "seek": 24106, "start": 246.82, "end": 250.66, "text": " It would really significantly slow the computer system down.", "tokens": [50652, 467, 576, 534, 10591, 2964, 264, 3820, 1185, 760, 13, 50844], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 64, "seek": 24106, "start": 250.66, "end": 254.58, "text": " So when we load a program, what we're actually doing is transferring data from secondary", "tokens": [50844, 407, 562, 321, 3677, 257, 1461, 11, 437, 321, 434, 767, 884, 307, 31437, 1412, 490, 11396, 51040], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 65, "seek": 24106, "start": 254.58, "end": 259.86, "text": " storage, the hard drive, into primary storage, RAM, random access memory.", "tokens": [51040, 6725, 11, 264, 1152, 3332, 11, 666, 6194, 6725, 11, 14561, 11, 4974, 2105, 4675, 13, 51304], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 66, "seek": 24106, "start": 259.86, "end": 261.1, "text": " Can you say that out loud?", "tokens": [51304, 1664, 291, 584, 300, 484, 6588, 30, 51366], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 67, "seek": 24106, "start": 261.1, "end": 262.54, "text": " Probably not yet.", "tokens": [51366, 9210, 406, 1939, 13, 51438], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 68, "seek": 24106, "start": 262.54, "end": 265.66, "text": " So there's a problem though with this.", "tokens": [51438, 407, 456, 311, 257, 1154, 1673, 365, 341, 13, 51594], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 69, "seek": 24106, "start": 265.66, "end": 269.66, "text": " If you've got too many programs running, if you've loaded too many programs, you're", "tokens": [51594, 759, 291, 600, 658, 886, 867, 4268, 2614, 11, 498, 291, 600, 13210, 886, 867, 4268, 11, 291, 434, 51794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15286831628708614, "compression_ratio": 1.6845637583892616, "no_speech_prob": 0.0007672737119719386}, {"id": 70, "seek": 26966, "start": 269.66, "end": 273.62, "text": " going to run out of this primary storage known as RAM.", "tokens": [50364, 516, 281, 1190, 484, 295, 341, 6194, 6725, 2570, 382, 14561, 13, 50562], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 71, "seek": 26966, "start": 273.62, "end": 276.1, "text": " And you've probably heard numbers relate to your computer systems.", "tokens": [50562, 400, 291, 600, 1391, 2198, 3547, 10961, 281, 428, 3820, 3652, 13, 50686], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 72, "seek": 26966, "start": 276.1, "end": 281.3, "text": " It's not uncommon that a computer will have, say, four or eight gigabytes of RAM, and", "tokens": [50686, 467, 311, 406, 29289, 300, 257, 3820, 486, 362, 11, 584, 11, 1451, 420, 3180, 42741, 295, 14561, 11, 293, 50946], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 73, "seek": 26966, "start": 281.3, "end": 283.38000000000005, "text": " you'll have like, terabytes of storage.", "tokens": [50946, 291, 603, 362, 411, 11, 1796, 24538, 295, 6725, 13, 51050], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 74, "seek": 26966, "start": 283.38000000000005, "end": 287.78000000000003, "text": " So RAM is really, really small, relatively, to the secondary storage.", "tokens": [51050, 407, 14561, 307, 534, 11, 534, 1359, 11, 7226, 11, 281, 264, 11396, 6725, 13, 51270], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 75, "seek": 26966, "start": 287.78000000000003, "end": 292.22, "text": " And so the problem we had is if we've loaded too many programs into RAM, we start to run", "tokens": [51270, 400, 370, 264, 1154, 321, 632, 307, 498, 321, 600, 13210, 886, 867, 4268, 666, 14561, 11, 321, 722, 281, 1190, 51492], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 76, "seek": 26966, "start": 292.22, "end": 293.78000000000003, "text": " out of RAM.", "tokens": [51492, 484, 295, 14561, 13, 51570], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 77, "seek": 26966, "start": 293.78000000000003, "end": 297.98, "text": " And a computer system, if it were to run out of memory entirely, the system would crash.", "tokens": [51570, 400, 257, 3820, 1185, 11, 498, 309, 645, 281, 1190, 484, 295, 4675, 7696, 11, 264, 1185, 576, 8252, 13, 51780], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14395484057339755, "compression_ratio": 1.8237410071942446, "no_speech_prob": 0.0013851812109351158}, {"id": 78, "seek": 29798, "start": 297.98, "end": 300.22, "text": " And in fact, we used to see this a lot.", "tokens": [50364, 400, 294, 1186, 11, 321, 1143, 281, 536, 341, 257, 688, 13, 50476], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1309544073568808, "compression_ratio": 1.7073170731707317, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005172693054191768}, {"id": 79, "seek": 29798, "start": 300.22, "end": 302.74, "text": " So there used to be something called the blue screen of death.", "tokens": [50476, 407, 456, 1143, 281, 312, 746, 1219, 264, 3344, 2568, 295, 2966, 13, 50602], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1309544073568808, "compression_ratio": 1.7073170731707317, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005172693054191768}, {"id": 80, "seek": 29798, "start": 302.74, "end": 305.02000000000004, "text": " Hopefully, you'll never have to see that in your life.", "tokens": [50602, 10429, 11, 291, 603, 1128, 362, 281, 536, 300, 294, 428, 993, 13, 50716], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1309544073568808, "compression_ratio": 1.7073170731707317, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005172693054191768}, {"id": 81, "seek": 29798, "start": 305.02000000000004, "end": 309.70000000000005, "text": " But in Windows, if you had too many things loaded and the system ran out of RAM, ran out", "tokens": [50716, 583, 294, 8591, 11, 498, 291, 632, 886, 867, 721, 13210, 293, 264, 1185, 5872, 484, 295, 14561, 11, 5872, 484, 50950], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1309544073568808, "compression_ratio": 1.7073170731707317, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005172693054191768}, {"id": 82, "seek": 29798, "start": 309.70000000000005, "end": 321.42, "text": " of this primary storage, you'd actually get a blue screen, the system would crash.", "tokens": [50950, 295, 341, 6194, 6725, 11, 291, 1116, 767, 483, 257, 3344, 2568, 11, 264, 1185, 576, 8252, 13, 51536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1309544073568808, "compression_ratio": 1.7073170731707317, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005172693054191768}, {"id": 83, "seek": 29798, "start": 321.42, "end": 326.18, "text": " So a way that we found, the industry is found to actually deal with this problem is to use", "tokens": [51536, 407, 257, 636, 300, 321, 1352, 11, 264, 3518, 307, 1352, 281, 767, 2028, 365, 341, 1154, 307, 281, 764, 51774], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1309544073568808, "compression_ratio": 1.7073170731707317, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005172693054191768}, {"id": 84, "seek": 32618, "start": 326.18, "end": 328.02, "text": " what is known as virtual memory.", "tokens": [50364, 437, 307, 2570, 382, 6374, 4675, 13, 50456], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 85, "seek": 32618, "start": 328.02, "end": 334.42, "text": " And this is the concept, drooly face, where we move some data out of RAM back to the hard", "tokens": [50456, 400, 341, 307, 264, 3410, 11, 3789, 16453, 1851, 11, 689, 321, 1286, 512, 1412, 484, 295, 14561, 646, 281, 264, 1152, 50776], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 86, "seek": 32618, "start": 334.42, "end": 335.42, "text": " drive.", "tokens": [50776, 3332, 13, 50826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 87, "seek": 32618, "start": 335.42, "end": 337.86, "text": " And we temporarily store it on the hard drive until it's neat again.", "tokens": [50826, 400, 321, 23750, 3531, 309, 322, 264, 1152, 3332, 1826, 309, 311, 10654, 797, 13, 50948], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 88, "seek": 32618, "start": 337.86, "end": 342.42, "text": " And then we can move it again back from the hard drive, woo, we were falling, back into", "tokens": [50948, 400, 550, 321, 393, 1286, 309, 797, 646, 490, 264, 1152, 3332, 11, 21657, 11, 321, 645, 7440, 11, 646, 666, 51176], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 89, "seek": 32618, "start": 342.42, "end": 343.42, "text": " primary storage.", "tokens": [51176, 6194, 6725, 13, 51226], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 90, "seek": 32618, "start": 343.42, "end": 345.5, "text": " And that's the concept of virtual memory.", "tokens": [51226, 400, 300, 311, 264, 3410, 295, 6374, 4675, 13, 51330], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 91, "seek": 32618, "start": 345.5, "end": 349.38, "text": " It's simply this idea that some data that's not being used very often is moved out of", "tokens": [51330, 467, 311, 2935, 341, 1558, 300, 512, 1412, 300, 311, 406, 885, 1143, 588, 2049, 307, 4259, 484, 295, 51524], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 92, "seek": 32618, "start": 349.38, "end": 351.42, "text": " RAM onto the hard drive.", "tokens": [51524, 14561, 3911, 264, 1152, 3332, 13, 51626], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 93, "seek": 32618, "start": 351.42, "end": 354.34000000000003, "text": " And then when it's needed again, back into memory.", "tokens": [51626, 400, 550, 562, 309, 311, 2978, 797, 11, 646, 666, 4675, 13, 51772], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1792247744574063, "compression_ratio": 1.988235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 0.014856478199362755}, {"id": 94, "seek": 35434, "start": 354.34, "end": 357.61999999999995, "text": " With the overall effect, it definitely slows down the system.", "tokens": [50364, 2022, 264, 4787, 1802, 11, 309, 2138, 35789, 760, 264, 1185, 13, 50528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.35398187308475887, "compression_ratio": 1.17, "no_speech_prob": 0.11297844350337982}, {"id": 95, "seek": 35434, "start": 357.61999999999995, "end": 361.34, "text": " But the system keeps running, so that's virtual memory.", "tokens": [50528, 583, 264, 1185, 5965, 2614, 11, 370, 300, 311, 6374, 4675, 13, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.35398187308475887, "compression_ratio": 1.17, "no_speech_prob": 0.11297844350337982}], "language": "en"}